ions**\\n\\nI’m thinking about file class names and their rules, especially the ones containing the “$” character, which seems limited to test classes or files. There’s a note about avoiding “$” in test class names, yet I see that generated inner classes include it. It’s also stated that all top-level test classes should be public. Hm, maybe it’s about mapping dynamic-access report classes? It's a bit of a puzzle!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dynamic class loading**\\n\\nIt seems that Groovy’s runtime behavior might require dynamic class loading. I’m thinking about how metadata generation runs on the JVM, which could lead to issues if unsupported features arise in native applications. If we catch `UnsupportedFeatureError` early, I wonder how dynamic access to the `eval getMethods` will behave. It’s important to consider coverage via Java. I'll need to check existing tests and use `NativeImageSupport` only if it’s necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_c9f5mIq5FFnwBS6L5MiqEbl3|fc_094ef549e4dc7c850169ffc88f4a7481978890c4ac68217bff", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|UnsupportedFeature\" tests/src -g '*.groovy' -g '*.java' | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 626, "output": 863, "cacheRead": 15360, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16849, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778370690311, "responseId": "resp_094ef549e4dc7c850169ffc882a43c8197a617a7cfc3ad23cc"}}
